HEADWORD: Galvanocautery
<hw>Gal*van`o*cau"ter*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Cautery effected by a knife or needle heated by
the passage of a galvanic current.</def>⟦br⟧
